Hello there peoples. I finally did it. I broke up with satan today and he has left my apartment.
 500 days in the coming but i actually did it. he will be on a bus going 7 hours away to san fran to live off someone else . Let us hope that somehow he becomes something he can live with that is good for him and others through this. i am becoming that thing be it what it may and i don't know completely what it is. The 23rd  birthday happened... some people have a birthday that makes them say wtf?? yeah i know i say that a lot but 'da voices have been screaming it . (no there are not really voices) you are the crazy one for believing me.
     SAD RELIEVED A LITTLE LONELY BUT IT'S ALL FOR THE BETTER. IT WAS ABOUT 2 YEARS OF MY LIFE

Tomorrow is my birthday May 10th oh yeah . 23. i really didn't expect my life to be how it is when i turned 23 but if u ask anyone say 5 years ago what they'll be doing in 5 years they usually don't know. 
 Now how to celebrate? there is this leonard cohen thing i guess that'll be it and then go out. yeah this year i'll barely make plans and just see what happens.

                another thing..i think i hate to go to goth clubs in LA  it is so lame that i just want to be wasteddrunk as soon as i'm there...not that i hate my friends or whatever but really...when you want the pretentious people they seem to know it and hide.  
        Do I just tend to have some kind of hate for any place i live in...part of me changing is becoming more optimistic...hard for someone who loves sarcasm the way i do...
       I think of moving again   insomnia...it gets worse and worse... LA lkes to be a daytime city... the other people awake all night are tweaked out or doing drugs or working overnyght...haha or maybe running a donut shop

        those who dream by day are more cognizant than those who dream by night

The other day i was laying on a bed thinking that i always felt i had an accomplishment to make and i always had a strong force that i had this task to do ... that it would be part of my reasoning.. it was always with me and driving me... and now i let a thought seep in that it will be my very defeat. i have felt uneasy for days.. i went to san fran to get out of the smog and take a break before the overtime workweek next week. (which i am actually excited about) and i cannot shake this feeling from me ...i know i am a morbid person at times and mostly a sarcastic pessimist.. but i don't think i'm being dramatic or anything right now or these past / last days... i had a horrible time in san fran- not due to anything... just a bad trip i do not feel good -only wheni see the ocean crash or stare at stars etc., but it's feeling like i'm going to lose these things, i heard a wise woman say today that some older cultures look at nervous breakdowns as a path to the real being within yourself and like a kind of soul searching.. 
         so tonight at 3 i have a ride back to LA from craigslist and everything i guess is cool about it but that's the thing... I do not feel "cool" about it i feel troubled -especially since i was writing about the vast area of nothingness in between here and there andmy death and being done after i felt like i had no driven reason
              i have a half an hour if i do go so time to stop rant/typing typecasting

i watched people in the valley have "hail ball fights" today on the news... The excitement and scare of snow or ice has hit the sunny folk and they panic... oh it's so hilarious... i decided tonight to have some friends over some vodka and some japanese cult cinema.... Entrails of a Beautiful Woman, the sequel to Entrails of Virgin .. if U are into japanese cult murder sex flix then check them out.     
         Last night i actually ventured out, not too far but to a phillipino concert at a sushi club.. ah it was cool at least i hung out with friends and did something social..
      something i was meaning to say on here:  so whenever i take public transportation(especially LA) I get violent urges .. I want to take the Sheriff's gun and hold up the red line Metro for example or I picture the subway tunnel filling with blood washing over the train the tracks and the mexicans freaking out going wild in the blood... Oh see why I prefer to stay inside... I was expecting house guests again today but they are stranded in a strange place off the 5 freeway with 20$ cash , 3 gas stations and no town for 25 miles... oh and a broken car... what a great horror movie : Murder of The Drunk Hippies: Raggedy ANN and Andy never stood a chance.
      Now that rambling was fun for a moment but i'd rather go read

     i think that when you go back to a place where you felt extreme feelings and you sit in the same chair .you smell the same smells. you feel the same air. you feel those feelings. it sucks if they weren't good ones. you start same basic patterns -standing in the same place sleeping in the same position. ack it fuckin sux.
that is what is like for me to move back here -to my own hell. but i will  just move everything around. sit differently. create new neural associations.

The sun was still out when he did it. As he drove down the nameless backroads with menace on the forte' he contemplated which would be worse; to leave the victim alone, bewildered in the woods where he would surely die a nameless death, or to put him out of miserywith his own hands,saving him from unknown peril. Why is the unknown so frightening. More frightening than death in this man's reasoning. So he pulled off to the side of the road, got out and lifted the defenseless, tiny dog out of the car. Their eyes met for a long second. One set innocent the other sadistic.The dog ran around the immediate area a bit as The Man watched. The man raised the crowbar in hand, called the dog over, took one last look at the dog he had shared a home with for years and brought the crowbar down hard onto the side of the dog. The dog yelped in frantic, horrified bursts. Blood stained his coat. The man gasped.He hadn't done it hard enough.The sight and guilt attempted to creep in..But the man shut it out with a final deafening blow. He wiped the bloody crowbar off in the grass, telling himself what a martar he was for taking the responsibilty to save his pup from the "unknown". He drove home to help 6 year old son make flyers for his lost dog and best friend.
